{"word":"κατακούω","slug":"κατακούω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατακούω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>σομαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to hear and obey, be subject to</i> another, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to hearken</i> or <i>give ear to</i> one, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to hear plainly</i>, <el>τι</el> or <el>τινά</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}